7 SUBTITLE 8. EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN PREFERENCE PROGRAM.
8 14–801.
9 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
10 INDICATED.
11 (B) “COVERED PROCUREMENT” MEANS A PROCUREMENT THAT IS VALUED
12 AT LESS THAN $80,000,000.
13 (C) “ESOP BIDDER” MEANS A RESPONSIBLE BIDDER WHO UTILIZES AN
14 EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN APPROVED UNDER § 401(A) OF THE INTERNAL
15 REVENUE CODE.
16 (D) “ESOP OFFEROR” MEANS A RESPONSIBLE OFFEROR WHO UTILIZES AN
17 EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN APPROVED UNDER § 401(A) OF THE INTERNAL
18 REVENUE CODE.
19 (E) “NON–ESOP BIDDER” MEANS A RESPONSIBLE BIDDER WHO DOES NOT
20 UTILIZE AN EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN APPROVED UNDER § 401(A) OF THE
21 INTERNAL REVENUE CODE.
22 (F) “NON–ESOP OFFEROR” MEANS A RESPONSIBLE OFFEROR WHO DOES
23 NOT UTILIZE AN EMPLOYEE STOCK OWNERSHIP PLAN APPROVED UNDER § 401(A) OF
24 THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE.
25 (G) “PERCENTAGE PREFERENCE” MEANS:
26 (1) THE PERCENT OF THE LOWEST RESPONSIVE BID SUBMITTED BY A
27 NON–ESOP BIDDER BY WHICH A RESPONSIVE BID SUBMITTED BY AN ESOP BIDDER
28 MAY:
29 (I) EXCEED THE LOWEST BID; AND
30 (II) BE AWARDED A COVERED PROCUREMENT CONTRACT IN
31 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SUBTITLE; OR

